HEADWORD: Hornwork
<hw>Horn"work`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Fort.)</fld>
<def>An outwork composed of two demibastions joined by a curtain. It is
connected with the works in rear by long wings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

